(656, 219, 'Intermediate Level Syllabus', 'Duration: 16 hours | Level: intermediate | Topics: Advanced Scope & Change Management | Earned Value Management (EVM) | Resource Planning & Conflict Resolution | Procurement Management | Quality Management (PDCA, Six Sigma basics) | Communication Planning & Stakeholder Engagement | Risk Response Strategies & Risk Register | Project Scheduling with MS Project | Agile Project Management (Scrum, Kanban) | Lessons Learned & Project Closure | PMI Ethics & Professional Responsibility | Intermediate Project: Full Project Plan with Risk Register', 2),
(657, 219, 'Advanced Level Syllabus', 'Duration: 28 hours | Level: advanced | Topics: PMP Exam Preparation (All 5 Process Groups & 10 Knowledge Areas) | Program & Portfolio Management | Benefits Realization Management | Agile at Scale (SAFe, LeSS) | Organizational Change Management | Advanced Risk & Issues Management | Project Governance & Audit | Strategic Alignment of Projects | Virtual & Global Team Management | Crisis Management in Projects | Measuring Project Success & OKRs | Capstone: Mock PMP Exam + Full Project Case Study', 3);
