(1568, 523, 'Intermediate Level Syllabus', 'Duration: 18 hours | Level: intermediate | Topics: Advanced JOINs & Self Joins | Subqueries & Correlated Subqueries | Common Table Expressions (CTEs) | Window Functions: ROW_NUMBER, RANK, LAG, LEAD | Views & Materialized Views | Stored Procedures & Functions | Triggers & Events | Transactions & ACID Properties | Query Optimization & Execution Plans | Normalization (1NF, 2NF, 3NF, BCNF) | Working with JSON/XML in SQL | Intermediate Project: HR Database System', 2),
(1569, 523, 'Advanced Level Syllabus', 'Duration: 32 hours | Level: advanced | Topics: Advanced Performance Tuning & Indexing Strategies | Partitioning & Sharding | Replication & High Availability | Data Warehousing Concepts (Star/Snowflake Schema) | Dimensional Modeling | ETL using SQL | OLAP & Analytical Queries | Advanced Security: Roles, Grants, Row-Level Security | Cloud SQL (AWS RDS, Azure SQL, BigQuery) | NoSQL vs SQL Tradeoffs | Auditing & Compliance | Capstone: Data Warehouse Design & Implementation', 3);
